name: Lake Clifton Thrombolites car park
directions: Turn off Forrest Hwy onto Lake Clifton Rd, follow the signs to the thrombolites
comment: Composting toilets with no water available.   Bitumen car park and concrete paths, one grabrail in the stalls.  The doors are wide and the stalls large, there'd be room for a wheelchair or pram.  Doors open inwards and doors and locks are manual.     Parking is free,  no designated accessible parking.   Path and viewing area is accessible.

name: Cockburn Gateway Shopping Centre
directions: In the shopping centre, near the Commonwealth Bank.   NO GN BABY FACILITIES.   Go to the GN Parenting Room near the Food Court,  which is amazing.
comment:
Baby facilities only available within Men's and Women's toilets.   Room for prams, child and full size toilets, change and washing facilities.   Door opens inwards, door and lock are manual.   Accessible stall is separate and GN.  Has lowered toilet and basin, grabrails, bins for rubbish and sanitary disposal.  Door opens inwards, door and lock are electric. 

Comfortable waiting area near toilets with seating,  room for prams and trolleys,  TV and power points. Available during Centre open hours.

name: Cockburn Gateway Shopping Centre
directions: Enter shopping centre and follow signs.   Near food hall.
comment:
Wow.  Parenting room with change and bathing facilities,  comfy chairs,  lockable feeding rooms,  microwave and GN toilets with room for prams.   Electric sliding main door,  feeding room doors open inwards,  manual doors and locks. 

Accessible separate GN toilet has grabrails,  lowered basin and hand dryer,  sanitary and rubbish disposal.  Door slides to open,  door and lock are electric.   
Waiting area with comfy bench seat and TV.  

Lots of free parking, timed between 1 and 4 hours.   Available during Centre open hours.

name: BP Baldivis North
directions: Driving up from the South-West / Mandurah districts.  Turn off  Kwinana Freeway ,  exit is well signposted but the signs only say  "Service Area".
comment:
Complex with fuel, food, coffee and ATM.  Toilets are inside the complex   and available 24/7.

Full Parents Room  with electric door,  facilities to change and wash the baby,  nappy disposal bins,  feeding area with comfy chairs,  a microwave and GN toilet.  The toilet has room for a pram or wheelchair,  but no grabrails.   Contains high sink with booster steps, rubbish and sanitary disposal,  and syringe disposal.  Door opens inwards, door and lock are manual. 

Accessible stall is gender neutral and the sign includes Braille.   Has lowered toilet and basin,  grabrails,  bins for rubbish,  sanitary and syringe disposal,  effective hand dryer.   Door opens inwards, door and lock are manual.   When I visited the light was off,  I thought it was motion activated but it isn't.   Had to be switched on: switch has a light and can be reached from a wheelchair. 

Lots of free untimed parking, dedicated accessible parking spots beside the doors.
